{{Expand Italian|topic=culture|date=September 2010|Abele (Alfieri)}}
{{italic title}}
'''''Abele''''' is an [[Italy|Italian]] opera inspired on the first [[Bible|Bible's]] chapters by [[Vittorio Alfieri]] (1749–1803) which he described as a [[tramelogedia]]. It was written in 1786 and first published after Alfieri's death in 1804 in [[London]]. The play's characters can be divided in two groups:
The first group includes the firsts earth's residents after [[Genesis creation narrative|the creation]] ([[Adam]], [[Eve|Eva]], [[Cain]] and [[Abel]]) and the second group represents the spiritual beings ([[God]], [[Beelzebub]], Sin, Envy, [[Death]], [[Angels]] and [[Demons]]).<ref>[[:it:Abele (Alfieri)]], Retrieved 11 February 2013{{Better source|reason=per WP:CIRCULAR|date=September 2015}}</ref>

