{{Infobox company | name = Jerónimo Martins Polska, S.A. | logo = Biedronka logo.svg | foundation = 1995 | type = [[Joint-stock company]] | founder = Jerónimo Martins Group, Mariusz Świtalski | location = ul. Żniwna 5, [[Kostrzyn]], Poland | locations = 2,823 (2017) <ref> https://www.jeronimomartins.com/wp-content/uploads/com/2018/2017-Preliminary-Sales.pdf </ref> | area_served = Poland | key_people = Pedro de Castro Soares | industry = [[Retail]] | products = [[Discount store]], [[supermarket]] | revenue = {{increase}} [[EUR|€]]11.2 billion (2017) <ref> https://www.jeronimomartins.com/wp-content/uploads/com/2018/2017-Preliminary-Sales.pdf </ref> | homepage = [http://www.biedronka.pl biedronka.pl] }} '''Biedronka''' is the largest [[discount supermarket]] chain in [[Poland]] with 2,823 stores in 2017 <ref> https://www.jeronimomartins.com/wp-content/uploads/com/2018/2017-Preliminary-Sales.pdf </ref> and 55,000 employees (2015) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biedronka.pl/pl/sklepy|title=Stores|publisher=biedronka.pl|accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref> <ref>[http://biznes.onet.pl/wiadomosci/handel/biedronka-mocno-zyskuje-na-500-plus-ten-wykres-to-udowadnia/9ff2qm Biedronka mocno zyskuje na 500 plus. Ten wykres to udowadnia]</ref>. It is owned by the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] company [[Jerónimo Martins]]. The supermarket chain's name translates as "[[Coccinellidae|ladybug]]", with a cartoon ladybug as the company's logo.
Biedronka sells mainly local (Polish) products, many of which are manufactured under the company's own label. It is one of the most popular supermarket chains in Poland and is targeted at lower-income customers. It also sells some Portuguese-made products, mostly wine.<ref>[http://portugalskiswiat.com/o-firmie/ O firmie]</ref>
Biedronka has had a dominant position in Poland's grocery retail market for more than a decade, and its main competitor in Poland is [[Lidl]]. <ref> http://www.pap.pl/en/news-/news,1243631,polish-discount-retailer-biedronka-boosts-sales-by-132-pct-in-2017.html </ref>
