{{Infobox company | name = Conquest AM | logo = | type = Private Limited Liability Company | foundation = 2010 | location = [[Ireland]] | industry = [[Asset Management]] | homepage = [http://www.conquest.group/asset Conquest AM Web page] }}
'''Conquest Asset Management''' is an independent [[asset management]] services firm, part of Conquest Group founded in 2010 and owned by its directors. Its head-office is incorporated in [[Ireland]] and it also has a registered office in [[Luxembourg]] .
It focuses on investment in and management of infrastructure assets, usually on the so-called "core+" and "value added' assets mainly in the energy, transport and renewable energy industries, usually at late stage of development, prior to construction and also throughout operations of the assets. In 2016, it launched a fund in the climate change mitigation and renewable energy sector.<ref>{{cite web|title=Conquest Launches Its Renewable Power Equity Fund With a "Super Bond" Profile Dedicated to Institutional Investors|url=https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/conquest-launches-renewable-power-equity-165000409.html|publisher=Yahoo Finance|date= 16 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Conquest Raises €115M in First Close for its European Renewables Real Assets Fund|url=http://www.closingcircle.com/15278-2/|publisher=Closing Circle|date= 21 March 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|title=Conquest raises $124 million to hold renewable energy assets for the long term|url=http://impactalpha.com/conquest-raises-124-million-to-hold-renewable-energy-assets-for-the-long-term/|publisher=Impact Alpha|date= 27 March 2017}}</ref> In May 2017, it announced the acquisition of a portfolio of solar assets from [[Engie]] group.<ref>{{cite web|title=Conquest acquires 6 solar parks in France |url=https://www.afp.com/en/news/1314/conquest-acquires-6-solar-parks-france-solairedirect|publisher=AFP|date= 24 May 2017}}</ref>
