'''Gabonese literature''', like many African literatures, began as an oral tradition.

== Colonial writing ==
Many American and European, especially French, writers penned works on Gabon. Père Trilles is one of the main writers of these texts with ''Mille lieu's dans l'inconnu: de la côte aux rives du Djah (A Thousand Leagues Into the Unknown: From the Coast to the Banks of the Djah).<ref>{{cite web|title=Gabonese literature at a glance|url=http://aflit.arts.uwa.edu.au/CountryGabonEN.html|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref>

