'''Galão''' ({{IPA-pt|ɡaˈlɐ̃õ|}}) is a hot drink from [[Portugal]] made of [[espresso]] and foamed milk. Similar to [[caffè latte]] or [[café au lait]], it consists of about one quarter coffee and three quarters foamed milk. It is served in a tall glass, as opposed to the smaller [[Garoto (coffee)|garoto]] that is served in a [[demitasse]]. When the proportion is 1:1 it is called ''meia de leite'' (half of milk) and it comes in a cup.

