2012 was designated as the '''International Year of Cooperatives''' by the [[United Nations General Assembly]] on 18 December 2009.<ref>{{cite web |date=18 December 2009 |title=United Nations General Assembly Resolution 64/136: Cooperatives in social development |url=https://documents-dds-ny.un.org/doc/UNDOC/GEN/N09/469/99/PDF/N0946999.pdf |publisher=[[United Nations General Assembly]] |accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>

The designation honors the use of [[cooperative]] organizations to contribute to socio-economic development across the world.<ref>{{cite web |title=2012&nbsp;– International Year of Cooperatives |url=https://www.un.org/en/events/coopsyear/ |publisher=[[United Nations]] |accessdate=January 1, 2017}}</ref> It officially launched on 31 October 2011 with the theme "Cooperative Enterprises Build a Better World".<ref>{{cite press release |date=31 October 2011 |title=United Nations Launches Year-Long Celebration of Vital Role of Cooperatives in Sustainable Development |url=https://www.un.org/press/en/2011/dev2919.doc.htm |publisher=[[United Nations]] |accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> United Nations Secretary-General [[Ban Ki-Moon]] was invited to speak at the November 2011 summit of the [[International Co-operative Alliance]] to celebrate the designation.<ref>{{cite press release |date=16 November 2011 |title=International Co-operative Alliance launches 2012 International Year of Co-operatives |url=http://ica.coop/en/media/news/international-co-operative-alliance-launches-2012-international-year-co-operatives |publisher=[[International Co-operative Alliance]] |accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>

