{{Update|part=events that occurred during the international year of soils|date=July 2018}}
The '''International Year of Soils, 2015''' (IYS 2015) was declared by the [[Sixty-eighth session of the United Nations General Assembly]] on December 20th, 2013 after recognizing December 5th as World Soil Day.<ref >{{cite web|last=Lindbo|first=David|title=The International Year of Soils|url=https://www.soils.org/IYS|publisher=Soil Science Society of America|accessdate=15 May 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/opinion/columnists/year-ahead-will-be-a-good-time-to-focus-on-soils-importance-287401571.html "Year ahead will be a good time to focus on soil's importance"]. ''Winnipeg Free Press''.</ref>

The purpose of the IYS is to raise [[environmental awareness|awareness]] worldwide of the importance of [[soil]]s for [[food security]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Draft resolution submitted by the Vice-Chair of the Committee,  Ms. Farrah Brown (Jamaica), on the basis of informal consultations on  draft resolution A/C.2/68/L.21|url=http://www.fao.org/fileadmin/user_upload/GSP/docs/iys/World_Soil_Day_and_International_Year_of_Soils__UNGA_Resolution_Dec._2013.pdf|publisher=United Nations General Assembly|accessdate=22 May 2014}}</ref><ref>[http://www.telesurtv.net/english/news/FAO-Declares-2015-as-the-International-Year-of-Soil--20141204-0006.html "The United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization will a campaign to generate awareness around soil fertility and food secrurity." (sic)]. ''Telesur''.</ref> agriculture,<ref>[http://www.crestonnewsadvertiser.com/2014/12/09/year-long-salute-to-soil-underscores-need-to-focus-on-its-health/a2rlrcm/ "Year-long salute to soil underscores need to focus on its health"]. ''Creston News Advertiser''.</ref> as well as in [[mitigation of climate change]], [[poverty alleviation]], and [[sustainable development]].<ref>[http://www.registerstar.com/columnists/growing_the_land/article_691de5be-8244-11e4-85b5-3bfd9d96fa25.html "Sustainability starts with the soil"]. ''Register-Star''.</ref> 

A website, logo and activities for The International Year of Soil have been planned by an organization called The Global Soil Partnership.  Agricultural and environmental organizations around the world have planned local events to contribute to the special year.<ref>[http://www.ottumwacourier.com/news/news_briefs/cedar-creek-partnership-project-supports-international-year-of-soil/article_88b27432-f43e-54c0-b787-54ce571f4414.html "Cedar Creek Partnership Project supports International Year of Soil"]. ''Otumwa Courier Online''.</ref><ref>[http://www.farmersguardian.com/home/latest-news/soil-association-goes-back-to-its-roots-with-soil-campaign/67958.article "Soil Association goes back to its roots with soil campaign"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150116020259/http://www.farmersguardian.com/home/latest-news/soil-association-goes-back-to-its-roots-with-soil-campaign/67958.article |date=2015-01-16 }}. ''Farmers Guardian''.</ref><ref>[http://www.lancaster.ac.uk/news/articles/2014/tree-planting-launches-international-year-of-soil/ "Tree planting launches international year of Soil"]. Lancaster University''.</ref>

