{{Infobox company |name = Korea Institute of Industrial Technology |logo = [[File:Kitech.gif|Kitech]] |type = [[Governmental Company|Public]] |foundation = 1989 |location = [[Cheonan]], [[South Korea|Republic of Korea]] |area_served = Worldwide |homepage = www.kitech.re.kr }}
'''Korea Institute of Industrial Technology (KITECH)''' is a [[South Korea]]n government research institute, established in 1989 to help develop technologies for the domestic industry, with focus on export competitiveness and [[Small and medium enterprises|SMEs]].
South Korea's then Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy (MOTIE) established the Korea Academy of Industrial Technology (KAITEC) in 1989 to strengthen the technological base of [[small and medium enterprises]] (SMEs).<ref>{{cite web |title=H.E. Dr. Han Seung-soo President of the UN General Assembly |url=http://www.unicef.org/specialsession/press/pkbios.htm |date=May 2002 |publisher=United Nations |accessdate=2010-11-05}}</ref> KAITEC was later renamed as the Korea Institute of Industrial Technology (KITECH).<ref name="KITECH1996">{{cite book |title=Opportunities in Asia: An Assessment of Construction Trends, Needs, and Potential Collaborations : Report |year=1997 |publisher=Civil Engineering Research Foundation |isbn=978-0-7844-0257-3 |pages=189–191 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SY1qs-OsBy4C&pg=PA189&lpg=PA189#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2010-11-05}}</ref> Following a re-organisation of government research institutes in 1999, KITECH was the largest institute grouped under the Korea Research Council for Industrial Science and Technology (ISTK), currently under the supervision of the [[Ministry of Knowledge Economy]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Lee |first=Kong-rae |title=Public Research System as a National Knowledge Infrastructure of Korea |url=http://www.research.smu.edu.sg/irc/2008/Papers/Lee-Paper.pdf |publisher=[[Singapore Management University]] |accessdate=2010-11-05|year=2008}}</ref><ref name="KH_2010">{{cite web |title=State-funded research institutes need reform |url=http://www.koreaherald.com/specialreport/Detail.jsp?newsMLId=20100630000634 |date=2010-07-01 |publisher=[[Korea Herald]] |accessdate=2010-11-05}}</ref>
KITECH's focus is on the development and management of manufacturing technologies for SMEs.<ref name="KITECH1996"/> KITECH receives both government and private funding, and distributes most of its research grants to private companies.<ref name="KITECH1996"/> By the middle of the 1990s, KITECH's annual budget was around US$130 billion, and employed a staff of one thousand in five sub-institutes.<ref name="KITECH1996"/>
The institute conducted materials research into environmentally friendly manufacture of metal alloys, and sold the technology to the private sector for 28.2 billion won.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://joongangdaily.joins.com/article/view.asp?aid=2920650 |title=Research team to receive big payout |date=2010-05-19 |publisher=[[JoongAng Daily]] |accessdate= 2010-10-10}}</ref> It also fostered the exchange of technological know-how with foreign research institutes by creating the Global Venture Investment Center in Seoul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2000/03/10/2000031061210.html |title=Venture Center to Provide Access to German Technology |date=2006-03-10 |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |accessdate= 2010-10-10}}</ref> Together with Korea Railroad Research Institute (KRRI) and the company [[Hyundai Rotem|Rotem]], KITECH developed the [[HSR-350x]], a high-speed train with domestic technology.<ref name="EffectofHSR2005">{{cite journal |last1=Lee |first1=Hisung |last2=Moon |first2=Dae-Seop |title=NEXT GENERATION OF KOREA TRAIN EXPRESS (KTX) : PROSPECT AND STRATEGIES |journal=Proceedings of the Eastern Asia Society for Transportation Studies |volume=5 |pages=255–262 |year=2005 |url=http://www.easts.info/on-line/proceedings_05/255.pdf |accessdate=2010-10-10}}</ref> The institute also participated in the development of the android prototypes [[EveR-1]] and 2.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2006/05/04/2006050461016.html |title=Korea Unveils World's Second Android |date=2006-05-04 |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |accessdate= 2010-10-10}}</ref>
==External links== * [http://eng.kitech.re.kr/ Korea Institute of Industrial Technology KITECH]
