[[Image:Leti.png|thumb|upright=1.20|Map of Maluku archipelago. Moa is located in the central part of the archipelago.]] [[File:Leti Islands en.png|thumbnail]]
'''Moa''' is an [[Indonesia]]n island, at the center of the [[Leti Islands]], and one of the 92 officially listed [[List of outlying islands of Indonesia|outlying islands of Indonesia]]. Leti is located in southwest [[Maluku (province)|Maluku]] [[Provinces of Indonesia|province]]. The main town is [[Tiakur]].
The [[Leti language]], a member of [[Austronesian languages]] is spoken on Moa.
==See also== * [[Islands of Indonesia]] * [[Maluku Islands]] * [[Maluku (province)]]
== Transports == The island is served by the [[Jos Orno Imsula Airport]] {{airport codes|JIO}}.
