{{Infobox television channel | name = TVSA HD | logofile = TVSA logo BiH.png | logosize = 200px | logocaption = | logoalt = | logo2 = | established = 1998 | airdate = | launch = {{Start date|1998|06|29|df=y}} | closed date = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | picture format = [[16:9]] [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]]) | share = | share as of = | share source = | network = | owner = JP "Televizija Kantona Sarajevo" d.o.o. Sarajevo | parent = | key people = [[Zlatko Topčić]] | slogan = Sarajevska televizija | motto = | country = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | language = [[Bosnian language]] | broadcast area = | affiliates = | headquarters = [[Sarajevo]] | former names = | replaced names = | replaced by names = | sister names = | timeshift names = | web = {{url|http://tvsa.ba|www.tvsa.ba}} | terr serv 1 = Terrestrial signal | terr chan 1 = Territory of [[Sarajevo Canton]] | sat serv 1 = | sat chan 1 = | cable serv 1 = [[Telemach]] | cable chan 1 = Channel 8 | cable serv 2 = [[M&H Company]] | cable chan 2 = Channel 12 | sat radio serv 1 = | sat radio chan 1 = | iptv serv 1 = [[Moja TV]] | iptv chan 1 = Channel 34 | iptv serv 2 = [[SUPER TV (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|SUPER TV]] | iptv chan 2 = Channel 7 | iptv serv 3 = [[Bosna TV]] platform | iptv chan 3 = Channel 10 | online serv 1 = TVSA Player | online chan 1 = {{url|http://tvsa.ba/ba/tvsa_uzivo/|Watch live}} {{nowrap|(Bosnia and Herzegovina only)}} | 3gmobile serv 1 = }}
'''TVSA''' or '''Televizija Kantona Sarajevo''' is a [[public broadcasting|public]] TV channel founded by Assembly of [[Sarajevo Canton]]. Headquarters of TVSA is located in capital city of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Sarajevo]] (along with national and entity level public broadcaster&nbsp;– [[BHRT]] and [[RTVFBiH]]). It was established in 1998 and the program is mainly produced in [[Bosnian language]]. Thanks to TV shows from its own production, TVSA programming becomes recognizable and widely viewed television station in [[Sarajevo]]. TV shows promote multiculturalism and specific culture, tradition and customs characteristic for the Sarajevo area and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].
This television channel broadcasts a variety of programs such as news, talk shows, documentaries, sports, movies, mosaic, children's programs, etc.
[[Zlatko Topčić]] managed TVSA from 2013 to 2016.
